column4: so am i being shunned from the ubuntu community, because my question wasn't easy to answer.  I'm part of the way there.  why is my computer problem less valid than other peoples? if you can't answer my computer trouble just say so.
i've made things worse by following instructions from here.  the terminal at least used to try to download.
it used to go to 98% and fail.  but now it won't even start
what do you want me run
or   ps aux | pastebinit   if you have pastebinit installed
What's the timestamp of the lock file?   ls -l /var/lib/dpkg/lock
third of july... did the computer shutdown improperly around that date? like cable got disconnected or something?
maybe i force shut down the computer or something. i do that sometimes.  other people use this computer too.
In that case, it probably happened while a package manager was working, and so it was unable to release the lock.
That looks good :) Did it just magically start working again?

no i had to return my sources.list file to default.   i screwed with it while following a tutorial/walkthru online.  it told me to open sources.list delete and replace with some other text.  that i've been told was from system 7 and no longer supported
i got told that last part here @ #ubuntu
